         <OBJECT_CONTRACT ITEM="1">
            <TITLE>
               <P>Regional FM Services</P>
            </TITLE>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="79993000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>The purpose of this Prior Information Notice (PIN) is:</P>
               <P>a) to give advance notice that HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) are considering undertaking an exercise to establish 6 contracts for the provision of Facilities Management Services for separate Hard and Soft FM across three Regional Areas;</P>
               <P>(b) to gauge the market interest in taking part in this procurement;</P>
               <P>(c) to obtain supplier insight to support specification development; and</P>
               <P>(d) to invite all potential suppliers, including but not limited to those responding to the Invitation to Tender for the RM3830 Framework, to a Supplier Engagement Event to be held in April.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <VAL_ESTIMATED_TOTAL CURRENCY="GBP">230000000</VAL_ESTIMATED_TOTAL>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="79993000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UK"/>
               <MAIN_SITE>
                  <P>United Kingdom.</P>
               </MAIN_SITE>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>The Government Hubs programme is overseeing the structural reorganisation and transformation of the current estate. For HMRC this will see the current landscape of 170 offices reoriented into 13 modern Regional Centres.</P>
                  <P>The new model for HMRC’s Facilities Management will see requirements split into 3 Regional areas (North, South and Central) and each of these Regions will be split into Hard and Soft FM. The first contract to be awarded is expected to be Hard FM in the South and contracts are expected to cover all of the current and future sites within the Region.</P>
                  <P>Further details of the requirement will be provided at the supplier engagement event in April and prior to the ITT releases for each individual contract.</P>
                  <P>Please express your interest in this supplier engagement event by emailing the recipients detailed below:</P>
                  <P>andrew.vanson@hmrc.gsi.gov.uk</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <INFO_ADD>
                  <P>The event is to be held on 13.4.2018 in London and will cover; an overview of the HMRC estates transformation, FM Requirements, timelines, routes to market, Q and A session, tour of the Croydon Regional Centre and an opportunity to book 1-2-1’s.</P>
                  <P>To secure a place on the event suppliers must express their interest by 4.4.2018 to andrew.vanson@hmrc.gsi.gov.uk</P>
               </INFO_ADD>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
            <DATE_PUBLICATION_NOTICE>2018-06-01</DATE_PUBLICATION_NOTICE>
         </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
         <PROCEDURE>
            <CONTRACT_COVERED_GPA/>
         </PROCEDURE>
         <COMPLEMENTARY_INFO>
            <INFO_ADD>
               <P>The intention is to run these procurements as call-offs from the new CCS FM Framework (RM3830).</P>
               <P>Hard FM Requirements:</P>
               <P>— Lot 1b (FM 7 000 000 GBP-50 000 000 GBP) Soft FM Requirements,</P>
               <P>— Lot 1c (FM 50 000 000 GBP+).</P>
               <P>HMRC are working with CCS to determine the viability of this option and may need to consider other routes to market.</P>
               <P>To view this Notice, please click here:</P>
               <P>https://www.delta-esourcing.com/delta/viewNotice.html?noticeId=309339243</P>
               <P>GO Reference: GO-2018329-PRO-12140151</P>
            </INFO_ADD>
            <DATE_DISPATCH_NOTICE>2018-03-29</DATE_DISPATCH_NOTICE>
         </COMPLEMENTARY_INFO>
